EdTech Startup Concept: CodeCraft 🚀
The Core Insight
The gap isn't about what students know — it's about what they've never had to do under pressure, with real stakes, in a real environment. Most bootcamps and online courses still teach in isolation. CodeCraft simulates the actual workplace.

What is CodeCraft?
CodeCraft is an industry-simulation platform where students learn by doing — not by watching.
Instead of video lectures and MCQs, students join a simulated tech company inside the platform. They get assigned a role (junior developer), a team, a manager (AI-driven), a codebase, deadlines, and real tickets to solve — just like a real job.

The Product Suite
1. 🏢 SimWork — The Flagship Product
A browser-based workspace that mimics a real dev environment:

Students receive a Jira-style ticket board with actual bugs to fix, features to build, and PRs to review
They work inside an embedded VS Code-like IDE connected to a real GitHub repo
An AI tech lead reviews their code, gives feedback, and assigns next tasks
Weekly "sprint reviews" simulate standups and retrospectives

Monetization: ₹999–₹1,999/month subscription for students

2. 🎯 HireReady — B2B Corporate Assessment Tool
Sold to companies:

Companies define their actual tech stack and real problem types
Candidates apply and get assessed through simulated on-the-job tasks (not LeetCode puzzles)
Employers see a full work-sample portfolio, not just a score
Replaces traditional coding rounds with a 3-day mini-internship simulation

Monetization: ₹50,000–₹2,00,000/year SaaS license per company

3. 🎓 CollegeBridge — B2B2C University Partnership
Sold to engineering colleges:

Replace dry lab sessions with CodeCraft's simulation curriculum
Faculty dashboard to track student progress across real projects
Students graduate with a verified SimWork portfolio alongside their degree
Colleges get placement rate improvement — a direct incentive to buy

Monetization: ₹5–₹15 lakh/year per institution

The Go-To-Market Plan
Phase 1 — Build & Validate (Months 1–6)

Build the MVP: just the SimWork IDE + 5 curated project tracks (web dev, backend, data, DSA, DevOps)
Onboard 500 beta students for free from Tier-2/3 engineering colleges in Maharashtra and Karnataka
Collect outcome data: did they get hired? did their debugging skills improve?
Partner with 2–3 startups willing to hire directly from the platform

Phase 2 — Monetize Students (Months 7–12)

Launch paid subscriptions after proving placement outcomes
Introduce leaderboards, peer code reviews, and team-based projects
Build a referral loop: placed students refer batchmates
Target: 5,000 paying students at ₹1,200/month average = ₹60L MRR

Phase 3 — Go B2B (Year 2)

Launch HireReady for companies with the placement data as the sales pitch
Approach HR heads at mid-size product companies (Razorpay, Zepto, Postman tier)
Launch CollegeBridge with AICTE-alignment messaging to engineering colleges
Target: 20 companies + 10 colleges = ₹3–4 Cr ARR


